Round Off



Write a program to get a float value from the user and display it in the below-mentioned format.

HINT: Use ceil() and floor() functions from the header file.



Input & Output Format:

Input consists of one float value.

The output consists of one integer, its rounded-up value, and its rounded-down value.



Sample Input 1:

54.5



Sample Output 1:

54

55

54



Sample Input 2:

66.7



Sample Output 2:

66

67

66


Case 1
Case 2
Input (stdin)
54.5

Output (stdout)
54
55
54


++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

import java.util.*;
class Main
{
  public static void main(String args[])
  {
    Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
    float f = sc.nextFloat();
    System.out.println((int)Math.abs(f));
    System.out.println((int)Math.ceil(f));
    System.out.println((int)Math.floor(f));
  }
}
